  <lyrics>
    <verse name="v1">
      <lines>
        <line>I <chord name="G"/>come to the garden alone, While the <chord name="C"/>dew is still on the <chord name="G"/>roses;</line>
        <line>And the <chord name="D"/>voice I hear falling <chord name="G"/>on my ear, The <chord name="A7"/>Son of God dis<chord name="D"/>closes.</line>
      </lines>
    </verse>
    <verse name="c">
      <lines>
        <line>And He <chord name="G"/>walks with me, and He <chord name="D"/>talks with me,</line>
        <line>And He <chord name="C"/>tells me <chord name="D7"/>I am His <chord name="G"/>own;</line>
        <line>And the <chord name="G"/>joy we <chord name="B7"/>share as we <chord name="Em"/>tarry <chord name="C"/>there,</line>
        <line>None <chord name="G"/>other has <chord name="D7"/>ever <chord name="G"/>known.</line>
      </lines>
    </verse>
    <verse name="v2">
      <lines>
        <line>He <chord name="G"/>speaks, and the sound of His voice Is so <chord name="C"/>sweet the birds hush their <chord name="G"/>singing;</line>
        <line>And the <chord name="D"/>melody that He <chord name="G"/>gave to me, With<chord name="A7"/>in my heart is <chord name="D"/>ringing.</line>
      </lines>
    </verse>
    <verse name="v3">
      <lines>
        <line>I'd <chord name="G"/>stay in the garden with Him, Though the <chord name="C"/>night around me be <chord name="G"/>falling;</line>
        <line>But He <chord name="D"/>bids me go; thru the <chord name="G"/>voice of woe, His <chord name="A7"/>voice to me is <chord name="D"/>calling.</line>
      </lines>
    </verse>
  </lyrics>
